in a while.

43:42.995 --> 43:43.954
Dad, I-- I-- know that--

43:44.038 --> 43:45.539
Your mother would be proud,
and so am I.

43:46.749 --> 43:49.418
Okay!
Let's get moving, hmm?

43:51.545 --> 43:52.755
Hey, Dad.
Hmm?

43:55.090 --> 43:56.634
- Was it worth it?
- Getting married?

43:56.634 --> 43:58.427
- Of course it is.
- No, no.

43:59.303 --> 44:00.679
Serious thing, serious question.

44:02.848 --> 44:05.809
What I'm asking is, was marrying
Mom worth losing her?

44:07.394 --> 44:09.897
This isn't about me.

44:09.897 --> 44:12.483
It's about Clare.
I'm aging faster than I should,

44:12.483 --> 44:13.734
and I've seen enough
of the future

44:13.734 --> 44:16.028
to know that I'm not
gonna make it all the way, so...

44:18.822 --> 44:19.907
for Clare's sake.

44:21.992 --> 44:23.744
Was marrying Mom
worth losing her?

44:26.580 --> 44:28.665
- That's a big question.
- Well, it's a big day.

44:31.627 --> 44:32.628
Yeah.

44:34.880 --> 44:36.090
It wasn't easy...

44:37.049 --> 44:38.092
but it was worth it.

44:40.511 --> 44:41.512
Thanks.

44:42.388 --> 44:43.430
Because of you.

44:47.643 --> 44:49.436
I don't say it enough,
but it was worth it

44:49.520 --> 44:50.521
because of you.

44:54.066 --> 44:55.109
Give her a child.

44:57.152 --> 45:00.280
If you can't stay, do that.

45:02.074 --> 45:03.492
Give her a child.

45:04.827 --> 45:08.539
Well, there might be
a problem with that.

45:08.539 --> 45:10.165
Problems can be solved.

45:15.671 --> 45:16.797
Not this one, Dad.

45:18.298 --> 45:21.301
Guys, come on.
I gotta get you to the church.

45:21.385 --> 45:22.719
- Okay. We're coming.
- On time!

45:22.803 --> 45:24.388
- Oh, I know.
- There's kind of a joke about that.

45:24.388 --> 45:25.722
You'll see. Come on.

45:25.806 --> 45:28.142
I know about the joke, Gomez.
I've watched the video.

45:32.563 --> 45:34.606
I mean,
what's the point of this?

45:34.690 --> 45:36.608
I'm not gonna show up.
I'm not--

45:42.197 --> 45:46.326
No. You have gotta
be shitting me.

45:46.410 --> 45:49.621
- You have got to be shitting me.
- CLARE, 29: Hmm.

45:52.040 --> 45:54.168
What the fuck is he doing there?

45:54.168 --> 45:56.753
- He's getting married.
- Yeah. To my girlfriend!

45:57.504 --> 45:58.338
CLARE, 29:
Keep in mind,

45:58.422 --> 45:59.673
he remembers
watching these videos.

45:59.673 --> 46:01.091
- HENRY, 28: Why?
- HENRY, 36: <i>Asshole.</i>

46:01.175 --> 46:03.719
Oh, nice.

46:03.719 --> 46:06.388
Classy. Very classy.
In a church!

46:07.764 --> 46:09.016
He'll remember that too.

46:09.016 --> 46:11.643
Yeah, you make quite
an impression on the cameraman.

46:16.899 --> 46:17.983
Hi.

46:19.693 --> 46:21.361
I'm so sorry.
We're running very late,

46:21.445 --> 46:23.447
we're gonna have to bring
the bride in straight away.

46:23.447 --> 46:26.867
Oh, yeah. No problems.
Just lock and load!

46:32.706 --> 46:33.916
All right, remember,
don't let anyone

46:33.916 --> 46:35.542
get a good look at you
in case they notice

46:35.626 --> 46:36.793
how old and shitty you are.

46:36.877 --> 46:38.504
Oh, thanks, Gomez.
Way to calm my nerves.

46:38.504 --> 46:41.381
Oh, don't be nervous,
you'll crinkle.

47:17.209 --> 47:18.460
I thought you'd be angrier.

47:19.836 --> 47:21.630
I am angry.

47:21.630 --> 47:24.049
I'm gonna be angry
for a very long time.

47:24.049 --> 47:25.801
Now shut up and admire my dress.

47:55.998 --> 47:57.332
<i>Thanks, Dad.</i>

47:59.167 --> 48:01.336
Yep. Now she's getting it.

48:12.514 --> 48:15.225
- Where is he?
- You look amazing.

48:15.309 --> 48:16.768
You smell of shoe polish.

48:17.728 --> 48:20.522
- You must be glad I hit him.
- Why?

48:21.690 --> 48:23.400
I saw your face.
I saw you fighting.

48:23.400 --> 48:25.611
- You-- you hated him.
- No, I never hate him.

48:25.611 --> 48:27.863
<i>Dearly beloved, we have
come together into the house...</i>

48:27.863 --> 48:29.239
I mean, I could punch
his stupid,

48:29.323 --> 48:31.617
thoughtless little face in,
but I could never hate him.

48:33.535 --> 48:34.745
HENRY, 28: What's he doing?

48:35.704 --> 48:36.705
Remembering.

48:37.372 --> 48:38.373
I love you.

48:38.457 --> 48:39.958
<i>...Clare and Henry.</i>

48:40.042 --> 48:41.001
Asshole.

48:41.001 --> 48:42.252
<i>Have you come here,</i>

48:42.336 --> 48:44.838
to enter into marriage
without coercion,

48:44.838 --> 48:46.798
freely and wholeheartedly?

48:46.882 --> 48:48.592
- I have.
- I have.

48:48.592 --> 48:50.385
Are you prepared
to accept children,

48:50.469 --> 48:52.346
lovingly from God?

48:52.346 --> 48:53.639
<i>And to bring them up,</i>

48:53.639 --> 48:55.766
<i>according to the law of Christ
and his church?</i>

48:55.766 --> 48:57.559
- HENRY, 36: <i>I am.</i>
- CLARE, 20: <i>I am.</i>

48:58.644 --> 48:59.936
I hate what he did to you.

49:01.938 --> 49:05.150
CLARE, 29: Oh, he did
what he thought he had to.

49:05.150 --> 49:08.320
I guess 'cause he thought
I couldn't take it anymore.

49:08.320 --> 49:09.821
And... <i>- I, Henry...</i>

49:09.905 --> 49:12.658
...well, because
he definitely couldn't.

49:12.658 --> 49:14.451
Thing is, I wanted children.

49:16.036 --> 49:18.497
I wanted your children
more than anything in the world.

49:18.497 --> 49:20.874
- And I want that too.
- No.

49:20.874 --> 49:24.586
- In sickness and in health...
- You gave up after five tries.

49:24.670 --> 49:25.962
...until death do us part.

49:26.046 --> 49:28.507
I would never have given up.
I would have done anything.

49:31.468 --> 49:32.886
So how are you gonna forgive me?

49:34.262 --> 49:36.682
I, Clare, take you, Henry...

49:36.682 --> 49:38.725
I guess I'm gonna have
to figure that one out.

49:38.809 --> 49:40.102
CLARE, 20:
<i>To have and to hold</i>

49:40.102 --> 49:43.188
<i>from this day forward.
For better, for worse...</i>

49:43.188 --> 49:45.148
But I'm supposed
to make you happy.

49:45.232 --> 49:47.484
CLARE, 20:
<i>In sickness and in health...</i>

49:47.484 --> 49:49.277
Who told you that?

49:49.361 --> 49:52.155
To love and to cherish,
until death do us part.

49:54.908 --> 49:59.413
Oh! Look at that face.

50:01.665 --> 50:03.542
How old are you now?
Twenty-eight?

50:03.542 --> 50:04.668
Yeah.

50:05.877 --> 50:07.379
Twenty-eight.

50:08.630 --> 50:12.426
Mm. Hey, I'm the older woman.

50:12.426 --> 50:14.970
Finally! I like this.

50:17.514 --> 50:20.142
Henry, we're not supposed
to make each other happy.

50:22.269 --> 50:26.940
If we do, great,
but that's not the point.

50:29.818 --> 50:31.236
We're getting married.

50:32.362 --> 50:35.407
Not going on a hot date,
or a vacation,

50:35.407 --> 50:38.910
or a weekend away somewhere,
but, actually...

50:39.870 --> 50:41.079
getting married.

50:43.039 --> 50:44.207
I mean, look at us.

50:45.125 --> 50:46.168
Look.

50:48.336 --> 50:52.048
Do we look like
we're gonna go on vacation?

50:55.427 --> 50:56.928
It's like...

50:59.306 --> 51:03.018
...like setting sail,
into a storm.

51:04.436 --> 51:06.104
And you know for a fact,

51:06.188 --> 51:08.440
you both won't make it out
the other side.

51:08.440 --> 51:09.733
So what do you do?

51:12.611 --> 51:15.030
You cling on
for as long as you can,

51:15.030 --> 51:16.448
because you know,

51:17.657 --> 51:20.619
that this is as good
as anything ever gets.

51:25.373 --> 51:27.125
Make my happy days happier...

51:29.920 --> 51:31.838
make my sad days bearable.

51:34.424 --> 51:36.885
And if you forgive me
when I hurt you,

51:36.885 --> 51:38.512
I'll try to do
the same for you.

51:40.096 --> 51:41.097
Deal?

51:45.060 --> 51:46.228
Okay.

51:50.857 --> 51:52.108
I miss you.

51:54.069 --> 51:56.613
